==English==
===Etymology===
Via French from Latin ''[[cantare]]'', '''[[sing]]'''

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːnt|-ɑːnt]]

===Verb===
'''chant''', present participle '''[[chanting]]''', past and past participle '''[[chanted]]'''

# [[sing]], especially without instruments, and as applied to [[monophonic]] and pre-modern music
====Translations====
*Finnish: [[messuta]]
*French: cander

===Noun===
'''chant'''

# type of [[singing]] done generally without instruments and [[harmony]]

===Related Terms===
*[[enchant]]
*[[Gregorian chant]]
*[[incantation]]
